4 HR____ COMMENDING MS. ANSLEY LYONS FOR HER SERVICE AND
5 LEADERSHIP IN ADDRESSING FOOD INSECURITY IN JACKSONVILLE,
6 ALABAMA.
7
8 WHEREAS, it is fitting and proper that the members of
9 this legislative body recognize and honor those
10 distinguished individuals who, through exemplary dedication
11 and selfless service, have rendered invaluable contributions
12 to their communities and enhanced the quality of life for
13 the residents of this state; and
14 WHEREAS, one such notable individual is Ms. Ansley
15 Lyons of Jacksonville, Alabama, a passionate advocate for
16 hunger relief who has contributed more than 4,200 lifetime
17 volunteer hours in steadfast service to others; and
18 WHEREAS, Ms. Lyons recently led a community
19 initiative in which she designed, built, installed, and
20 stocked two Little Free Food Pantries in Jacksonville; these
21 pantries serve as a reliable and accessible source of food
22 for individuals and families in need while fostering a
23 spirit of generosity and mutual support within the
24 community; and
25 WHEREAS, in addition to this noteworthy endeavor, Ms.
26 Lyons volunteers weekly at the Jacksonville Christian
27 Outreach Center, where she plays a vital role in the
28 distribution of food to local families facing hardship; and
