29 WHEREAS, Ms. Lyons balances her extensive service
30 commitments with her academic pursuits as a full-time
31 student at Jacksonville State University, where she is
32 working toward a Bachelor of Fine Arts degree and is
33 expected to graduate in April 2026 with a perfect 4.0 grade
34 point average; and
35 WHEREAS, Ms. Ansley Lyons' steadfast dedication to
36 alleviating food insecurity reflects the highest ideals of
37 public service and exemplifies exceptional integrity,
38 compassion, and an unwavering commitment to the well-being
39 of others; and
40 WHEREAS, the residents of Jacksonville and the State
41 of Alabama benefit immeasurably from her tireless efforts,
42 selflessness, and enduring devotion to improving the lives
43 of those around her; now therefore,
44 BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE
45 LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA, That we do hereby most highly
46 commend Ms. Ansley Lyons for her exceptional service and
47 leadership in addressing food insecurity in Jacksonville,
48 and we extend to her our deepest appreciation, admiration,
49 and sincere best wishes for continued success and
50 fulfillment in all the years to come.
